4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING THE GROW YOUR OWN GRANT
5 PROGRAM; PROVIDING THAT POSTSECONDARY INSTITUTIONS ARE ELIGIBLE FOR GRANTS UNDER
6 THE PROGRAM; REVISING THE REQUIREMENT FOR EARNING POSTSECONDARY CREDITS WHILE IN
7 HIGH SCHOOL; REMOVING THE REQUIREMENT FOR THE COMMISSIONER OF HIGHER EDUCATION
8 TO CONVERT A GRANT TO A LOAN IN CERTAIN CIRCUMSTANCES; EXTENDING THE TERMINATION
9 DATE FOR THE GROW YOUR OWN GRANT PROGRAM; PROVIDING A DEFINITION; PROVIDING AN
10 APPROPRIATION; AMENDING SECTION 20-4-601, MCA; AMENDING SECTION 6, CHAPTER 514, LAWS
11 OF 2021; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
14
15 Section 1. Section 20-4-601, MCA, is amended to read:
16 "20-4-601. (Temporary) Grow your own grant program -- administration. (1) There is a grow your
17 own grant program administered by the commissioner of higher education. The purpose of the grant program is
18 to develop teacher pipelines aimed at serving rural and reservation school districts.
19 (2) (a) The grow your own grant program must involve:
20 (i) the opportunity for students to take dual credit courses in education while in high school;
21 (ii) the opportunity for students to engage in work-based learning opportunities in the field of
22 education; and
23 (iii) collaboration between school districts and institutions of higher education in developing a
24 career pathway for education.
25 (b) The grant program must allow and encourage small and proximate districts to collaborate in
26 developing their grow your own grant programs.
27 (c) A school district is eligible for the program if the district has one or more schools impacted by a
28 quality educator shortage.
